Class
Description
ClassDatabase
Holds the fitness class schedule and also provides functionality such as checking in, dropping, and displaying the schedule
ClassSchedule
An array-based linear data structure that hold the list of fitnessclasses, also provide the methods for managing classes as well as displaying them
DatabaseManager
This singleton class stores and manages all the databases in this application, current the member and the class database.
Date
Represents a Calendar Date
DateTest
JUnit Test class for Date.isValid()
Family
Family class that represents a family membership, extends the Member class and includes specific data and operations to a family membership;
FitnessClass
Defines a fitness class the members can check in
FitnessClassTest
JUnit Test class for Premium.membershipFee() Note: Our implementation does not do error checks in the FitnessClass class, instead it does the checks a few layers before when the client inputs the command, so the Member that is being passed into these methods will ALWAYS be valid, no need to test the cases of invalid members here.
GymManagerController
The Controller class responsible for the "control" of the application contains FXML injections and control node functionalities Implements Initializable for initializing class fields and fxml elements
GymManagerMain
The main class to "launch" the GUI Client
Location
enum class representing the Location of a member, contains info about the location
Member
Member class that stores all member info
Member.CompareMode
Used to toggle between different sorting modes
MemberDatabase
An array-based linear data structure that hold the list of members, also provide the methods for managing the list of members
MemberType
An enum representing the type of a Member
MemberValidator
This class is mainly responsible for validating member info from client input, also displays error messages when there is an invalid input.
Premium
Premium class that represents a premium membership, extends the Family class and includes specific data and operations to a premium membership;
PremiumTest
JUnit Test class for Premium.membershipFee()

Represents a Time in a day
